OL,5,FThough the THC content of the flower
OL,6,Fwas below 0.2% (within the legal
OL,7,Fthreshold), the flower itself sits in
OL,8,Fthis so-called legal "grey area,"
OL,9,Faccording to suppliers.
OL,11,FThe case went to the Court of Appeal,
OL,12,Fwhich ruled in favour of the CBD
OL,13,Fcompany.
OL,15,FJudges said they did not consider
OL,16,Fflower with a THC content below 0.2% a
OL,17,F"narcotic drug" and so ruled that the
OL,18,Fcompany could not have broken the law
OL,19,Funder the Misuse of Drugs Act.
